content: An edit to my previous review: I have indeed reported as many men and underage users as possible. I don't often write reviews, but I feel I need to say that my experience with Zoe was not at all pleasant. The interface was jumpy and often wouldn't follow directions, message notifications often wouldn't pop up for myself or the people I was chatting to, leading to us moving on to different apps. A pro to the app was the about you section where you could fit in all these little extra details, which I appreciated! A con to this: not a lot of people filled any of the bio or about me sections, half of the profiles were a single photo with no bio. I upgraded to premium despite all of this and found that nothing improved and premium did not help me in my search at all. Save your money. There was also a disturbing amount of men and underage females on the app that I reported (with their true age in their bio). I've used other popular and well known dating apps, and the ratio of underage users to of age users surpasses those apps ten-fold. I was highly uncomfortable talking to anyone my age in case they were lying about their age. There's some potential to this app, but for me, I'll be steering clear.
replyContent: Hi, thank you for your feedback. We are sorry to hear our app hasn't fulfilled your expectations. We are working to improve our app all day long so it'll help us a lot if you could report those accounts - tap on the profile and then hit ‚ÄúMore‚Äù in the upper left corner and choose ‚ÄúReport and Block".
